Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Susanna Hoffs (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Susanna Hoffs (pictured) sang on the studio recording of "Eternal Flame" naked after producer Davitt Sigerson pranked her by saying that Olivia Newton-John had done the same thing?

entry.title: On the German Republic (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Thomas Mann insisted on omitting a passage on homoeroticism in the English translation of his work "On the German Republic"?

entry.title: Cruise of the Kings (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that more than 100 European royals boarded the Cruise of the Kings, a 1954 cruise organised by the Greek queen consort Frederica of Hanover to promote tourism in Greece?

entry.title: Le Moniteur Acadien (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the first Acadian newspaper, Le Moniteur Acadien, was acquired in 2023 for just CA$1?

entry.title: NCVs (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that NCVs can assign different values to the lives of civilians of different nationalities?

entry.title: My Beautiful Man (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Yuu Nagira, the author of My Beautiful Man, did not expect readers to love one of the main characters because she had written him to be creepy?

entry.title: Agnes Mapes (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that actress Agnes Mapes had to improvise a complex choreographed dance from basic poses for the 1907 play The Holy City?

entry.title: Sonja van den Ende (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that in March 2022 Sonja van den Ende was the only Dutch journalist to report from the Russian-occupied Donbas on the war in Ukraine?

entry.title: a Thai hotel (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a restaurant in a Thai hotel serves "Chicken Volcano", a dish containing whiskey?
